#BlackLivesMatter. Like many, I grieve the senseless murder of George Floyd and countless other black Americans. The racism that plagues our country is unacceptable. While as a white man I have not experienced racism and its anguish firsthand, I stand in support of those who have and acknowledge the need to deeply transform as a country. We have to do better to eliminate all forms of racism and inspire positive, permanent change. I have always believed that actions speak louder than words, but I felt it was necessary and important to add my voice to help advance things in any way I can. captions: We got to take in a little bit of God’s beautiful and wonderful creation at the refuge Saturday! Appreciating it with @chewing00 made it even better!
Our lives may send us in multiple directions, but I can always count on this guy to make me smile no matter where we are!

This beautiful friend of mine is getting married today!! @perrykatherinefurr I can’t wait to stand by your side as you unite in Christ with such a sweet and kind-hearted man. I love you and am so thankful for our friendship through the years!! #thepriceisright
Can’t wait to try out all of these sweet new products! Thank you!! @everettsportsmarketing @nobullproject @drunkelephant @thephoozy @spikeball @hfactorwater @slimclipcase @lululemon @bonk_breaker

What an amazing week experiencing my first @solheimcup2019! Hats off to the European Team on a hard earned victory. This team, the captains and caddies made for an unforgettable week. From the highs to the lows, we learn and we grow as players and individuals. We are the United States of America, and I couldn’t be more proud to have worn the red white and blue this week! Thanks to the amazing fans, volunteers, and those working behind the scenes. I couldn’t be here without the love and support of so many back home, and especially the ones who made the last minute trip across the pond! Love y’all! 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸

Thank you @cpwomensopen for a great week! It’s always a treat to play in Canada at such a premiere event! Unfortunately I didn’t play well enough to earn a spot on the Solheim Cup team, but I know God’s will is greater than everything else. Representing the United States at the Solheim Cup is something I’ve always dreamed of doing, so not making the team really stung! I know that this will only motivate me more for 2021, and I will continue to work hard to try and earn the spot in 2 years! For now, I’ll cheer on Team USA and wish everyone on the team nothing but the best! 🇺🇸 Thanks as always to my friends, family and sponsors for the constant support! •••• @pingtour @speedwaystores @renasantbank @titleist @footjoy @sparms.official @antiguasportswear

I cannot express how much joy was filled in my heart from these past couple of days at the @speedwaystores Miracle Tournament for @cmnhospitals! I had the privilege of being a very very small part of Speedway’s continuous and generous efforts to raise money for these kids and many others in the 170 member hospitals across the US and Canada! So many children and families are in need of speciality pediatric services, and it’s amazing to see so many people come together to reach these kids and families in need of the best care to face different conditions head on. The fight in these kids and the smiles across their faces, no matter what they are going through, are a huge part of why I’m so blessed to do what I do! I am beyond thankful! God is so powerful, and I know great things will come from this amazing event. #playyellow

Wow!! What a great week @shopritelpga! Thank you to the volunteers and everyone who made the event possible. It felt great to be in contention down the stretch on Sunday! Congrats @lexi on the win! Always fun competing against the best in the world. @kpmgwomenspga  next!

What an amazing week in Charleston! Thank you @usga for a world class event. Out of 5 tries, this was the quality golf I’ve been looking for in our national championship. I’m so thankful my family and friends were able to be with me throughout this week and support through the tiring and hot days! I’m forever grateful and am always blown away by the blessings that flow through Christ!! Thanks again to @porterconradjewelry for keeping me stylish this week and thanks to all my sponsors!  @speedwaystores @renasantbank @pingtour @carlhogantoyota @footjoy #Titliest  Photo creds: @usga @gettyimages

So sad to hear of the passing of Marilynn Smith this morning when we saw her just a couple of weeks ago. She made her mark by being a founding member of the @lpga_tour! She was a pioneer for the game and touched the lives of so many, including mine! Thank you for everything! 🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼

Excited to get the Australian Women’s Open started tomorrow. Knocked off some rust at the Vic Open last week, but hope to get rolling down under! @golfaust @isps_handa @southaustralia @cityofadelaide @pingtour @speedwaystores @renasantbank @titleist @footjoy @carlhogantoyota @oldwaverly

My family has never skipped a beat while traveling the U.S. with me, and they have provided more support than they will ever know and be thanked for! My coaches, teammates and fellow senior Rica Tse have been more than my team but my family too. This university has given me far more than I ever thought, and for that I am immensely grateful. My career as a collegiate golfer is now over, but I look forward to continuing my career as a golfer. God has blessed me profoundly! Also, a big Happy Mothers Day shout out to my Mom, Nanney, and Granny! Much love to everyone who has been with me on this journey!

In the elevator with some cute guys 👀 please read below: 
Please join my family, @jc7474, Lucca & myself, defeat DIPG and walk in the Superhero Sprint & 6k with us. Help us honor the amazing superheroes, the boys & girls who fought, and continue to fight childhood cancer. For those who don't know, DIPG stands for Diffuse Intrinsic Pontine Glioma. There's NO cure. Research is underfunded, and the survival rate is 0%. There's simply not enough research. Can you imagine the doctor telling you your child has a 0% chance to live? Let's change this. Walk with us! 
DIPG has stolen the lives of two children I know of in the Maryland area in the last year. Michael Mosier (who's mom started this race & her own foundation in honor of her son, who passed one year ago today) and Emma Hensel. Michael & Emma deserved to live. Every parent deserves to watch their children grow up. As moms, we go through the day to day with endless worries. I've come to notice, every stage comes with new anxieties. For most of us, they are just worries. To some, it's a real life nightmare they don't wake up from. Children's cancer needs as much fundraising as it can get. Event is on May 29th 
Race start- 8:30am
Location- 7101 democracy Blvd Bethesda Md 
Registration is $35 and $50 with a t-shirt. Link to register is in my bio. We look forward to seeing you all there!

This is sweet Emma. Less than 2 months ago, she was living a normal 3 year old life. Now, she's losing her life day by day. Emma will never have her first day of kindergarten, a sweet 16, a first kiss, prom, first day of college, or get married; all of these milestones we live for as parents. A quote is below from her amazing mother, Teal) 💜💜💜
My husband & I, along with Karl Alzner, Brooks Orpik, Nicklas Backstrom & their partners, will be holding a fundraiser for this family. Mark your calendars for February 19th at 5pm @ Don Tito's in Arlington. The owner has graciously offered to give a percentage of food/drink sale to this family & we will be charging admission at the door. #emmastrong A more formal flyer will be made later💜💜💜
"It is with pure shock that I confirm, our sweet angel, Emma Rose Hensel, 3 years-old was diagnosed at Ruby Memorial by a team of Doctors from around the country with Difuse Intrinsic Pontine Glioma. This is an inoperable brain tumor, with no known cure. Emma was given up to a year with us. There are no words right now, beyond “we are living a nightmare”. Emma’s best friend and almost 6-year old sister, Lily Kayleen Hensel, knows only her sister is ill. It is with a humble heart that my husband, Jason and I thank everyone who has offered support. We do not know what we need, besides a miracle.." 💜💜💜
The last thing this family needs to worry about is money. They need to spend every moment cherishing their time with Emma. #emmastrong #curechildhoodcancer #washingtoncapitals #ihatecancer Emma's favorite color is purple 💜💜💜
